Context("LimitedNumeric");

$b=random(2,4,1);
$a=random($b**2+1,$b**2+5,1);
$c=random(2,5,1);

$ans = ($a-$b)**2+$c*($a-$b**2);
$ans=Compute($ans);

##############################################

TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PGML

Evaluate the following.

    [`` ([$a]-[$b])^{2}+[$c]([$a]-[$b]^{2}) = ``][________]{$ans}

END_PGML

##############################################

$s1=($a-$b)**2;
$s2=$c*($a-$b**2);

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

When doing complicated order of operations problems, it's critical to go step by step. Don't try to do two steps at once.

    [``
\begin{aligned}[t]
   &\phantom{{}=} ([$a]-[$b])^{2}+[$c]([$a]-[$b]^{2}) \\
   &= [$a-$b]^{2}+[$c]([$a]-[$b]^{2}) \\
   &= [$a-$b]^{2}+[$c]([$a]-[$b*$b]) \\
   &= [$a-$b]^{2}+[$c]([$a-$b*$b]) \\
   &= [$s1]+[$c]([$a-$b*$b]) \\
   &= [$s1]+[$s2] \\
   &= [$ans]
\end{aligned}
    ``]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

